attributes.Long form description: The student has to operate a Nintendo Switch. The student removes the Joy-Con controllers from the Nintendo Switch, then the student assembles the Joy-Con controllers to the comfort grip and is instructed to attach the Joy-Con strap, the student attaches the red Joy-Con controller to the Joy-Con strap, but has difficulties assembling the blue Joy-Con controller, the instructor tells him to try in the other way and the student finally attaches the Joy- Con strip to the Joy-Con controller. For the next step the student attaches the Joy-Con controllers to the Nintendo Switch and opens the kickstand that is on the back, the student removes the game cartridge and asks to what should be change the game cartridge, the instructor says they are just going to pretend to change it, so the student inserts again the same game cartridge, next the student has to change the SD card, and performs this instructions. Lastly the student has to turn on the Nintendo Switch, he presses the button, but the Nintendo doesn't turn on, so the instructor asks to hold the button for some seconds, after the student does this, the nintendo switch turns on, and the student turns off the Nintendo Switch by pressing the same button.
